    <item>
      <title>Motor Control board DIM Connection Viewer</title>
      <link>https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/experimental/dim_viewer/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/experimental/dim_viewer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Interactive browser of every signal that crosses the &lt;strong&gt;120-pin MCS DIM connector&lt;/strong&gt; between a&#xA;Motor Control DIM card (the MCU board) and a motor-control baseboard — built &lt;strong&gt;for&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreferrer&#34;&gt;MPLAB Device Blocks&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;developers&lt;/strong&gt; wiring a Simulink model to a given DIM + baseboard.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;open-the-viewer&#34;&gt;Open the viewer&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p style=&#34;text-align:center; margin: 16px 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/tools/dim_viewer/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;     style=&#34;display:inline-block; padding:10px 22px; background:#0d6efd; color:#fff;&#xA;            border-radius:4px; text-decoration:none; font-weight:600;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    🖥️ Open in full window&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;iframe src=&#34;https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/tools/dim_viewer/&#34;&#xA;        title=&#34;Motor Control board DIM Connection Viewer&#34;&#xA;        loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width:100%; height:1100px; border:1px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px;&#xA;               box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); background:#fff;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Your browser does not support inline frames. Please&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://mplab-blockset.github.io/MPLAB-Device-Blocks-for-Simulink/tools/dim_viewer/&#34;&gt;open the viewer in a new window&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-to-read-a-pin-card&#34;&gt;How to read a pin card&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Each of the 120 DIM pins is one card, grouped into colour-coded &lt;strong&gt;category sections&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;(PWM, ANA, QEI, HAL, FLT, PFC, DBG, COM, LED, BTN, XPRO1, XPRO2, PWR, NC, …). The section&#xA;header names and colours the category, so there is no separate on-page legend.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
